----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A GENERAL DOCUMENT REVIEW
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Prompt Summary
Summarize the following document based on the given criteria:
✅ Summary Type: {summary_type}  
  (Options: "Concise (one paragraph)", "Bullet Points", "Detailed")  
✅ Length: {summary_length}  
  (Options: "Short (50 words or less)", "Medium (3-5 sentences)", "Long (200+ words)")
✅ Purpose: {summary_purpose}  
  (Options: "General Understanding", "Decision Making", "Executive Briefing")  
✅ Tone & Style: {tone_style}
  (Options: "Professional", "Casual", "Academic")
✅ Key Focus Areas: {focus_areas}
  (Options: "Key Insights", "Facts Only", "Implications for [specific topic]")
✅ Bias & Accuracy Control: {bias_accuracy}
  (Options: "Objective only", "Include interpretations", "Explicit content only")
✅ Format Requirements: {format_type}
  (Options: "Plain text", "Table format", "JSON output")
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Basic Document Details
✅ Title – The main title or heading of the document.
✅ Author(s) – Name(s) of the author(s) or contributors.
✅ Date – The date of publication or document creation.
✅ Document Type – Report, article, research paper, email, contract, etc.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Key Content Elements
✅ Summary – A brief synopsis of the document’s content.
✅ Main Topics – The core subjects discussed in the document.
✅ Key Insights & Takeaways – Important conclusions, findings, or recommendations.
✅ Keywords & Phrases – Frequently mentioned terms that define the document’s scope.
✅ Sentiment Analysis – The overall tone (positive, neutral, negative).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Entities (Named Entity Recognition - NER)
✅ People (Names) – Individuals mentioned in the document.
✅ Organizations – Companies, institutions, or groups referenced.
✅ Locations – Cities, countries, addresses, geographical places.
✅ Dates & Time References – Specific days, months, years, time ranges.
✅ Events – Conferences, historical events, meetings, project names.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Structured Data Extraction
✅ Numbers & Statistics – Financial figures, research data, percentages, etc.
✅ Monetary Values – Prices, budgets, revenues, expenses.
✅ Measurements – Units of weight, distance, volume, speed, etc.
✅ Legal References – Laws, regulations, contracts, compliance terms.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Actionable Elements
✅ Decisions & Recommendations – Key choices or actions suggested in the document.
✅ Action Items & Next Steps – Specific tasks or follow-ups required.
✅ Questions Raised – Unanswered questions or topics requiring further discussion.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Contextual Insights
✅ Comparisons & Contrasts – Differences and similarities between subjects.
✅ Citations & References – Other sources, studies, or documents mentioned.
✅ Implications & Consequences – Effects of the information presented.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Structural & Formatting Elements
✅ Headings & Subheadings – Sections and organization of content.
✅ Bullet Points & Lists – Key enumerations or structured points.
✅ Tables & Charts – Data representations and visual elements.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. Document Metadata (If Digital)
✅ File Type & Format – PDF, DOCX, TXT, HTML, etc.
✅ Word Count & Page Count – Document length.
✅ Readability Score – Complexity of the language used.
✅ Language Detection – Language(s) in the document.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9. Advanced Context & Thematic Analysis
✅ Underlying Themes & Motifs – Not just topics, but recurring ideas or metaphors.
✅ Hidden Agendas or Bias – Implicit perspectives, political or corporate bias.
✅ Contradictions & Inconsistencies – Points in the document that don’t align.
✅ Intent & Purpose Detection – Is the document informative, persuasive, misleading, etc.?
✅ Explicit vs. Implicit Claims – What’s stated outright vs. what’s implied?
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10. Social & Cultural Elements
✅ Cultural References – Mentions of cultural, religious, or historical elements.
✅ Idioms & Figurative Language – Metaphors, analogies, and unique phrasing.
✅ Socioeconomic Impact – How the document affects or references different social groups.
✅ Ethical & Moral Considerations – Discussions on ethics, fairness, or societal impact.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11. Deep Entity Recognition & Relationship Mapping
✅ Connections Between People – How individuals or organizations relate to each other.
✅ Hierarchy & Organizational Structure – Who reports to whom, roles, and influence.
✅ Industry & Sector Classification – Identifying which business or academic sector applies.
✅ Geopolitical Relevance – Global or regional influence of the document’s content.
✅ Mentions of Intellectual Property – Patents, copyrights, trademarks, proprietary tech.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12. Sentiment & Emotional Tone Analysis
✅ Emotion Detection – Fear, excitement, urgency, frustration, optimism.
✅ Persuasive Techniques – Emotional appeals, logical arguments, rhetorical questions.
✅ Public Perception Impact – How this document might influence opinions or trends.
✅ Trustworthiness & Credibility Score – Evaluating sources, citations, and factual accuracy.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
13. Advanced Data & Quantitative Analysis
✅ Trend Extraction – Identifying patterns over time within the document.
✅ Predictive Insights – Based on past data, what might happen next?
✅ Financial Implications – How this document affects money, business, or economy.
✅ Time-Sensitive Information – Information that may expire or change (e.g., stock prices, forecasts).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14. Legal, Compliance & Security Aspects
✅ Legal Liabilities & Risks – Any legal consequences implied in the text.
✅ Compliance Issues – Whether the content aligns with regulations (GDPR, HIPAA, SEC rules).
✅ Cybersecurity & Data Sensitivity – Any private or sensitive data leaks.
✅ Contractual Obligations – Binding clauses, obligations, warranties.
✅ Regulatory References – Specific mentions of laws, industry rules, or government policies.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
15. Media & Content Integrity
✅ Fact-Checking Needs – Statements requiring verification.
✅ Misinformation or Propaganda Indicators – Biased framing, misleading statistics, fake news patterns.
✅ Plagiarism & Originality – Whether parts of the text match external sources.
✅ Fake Reviews or Testimonials – If the document includes product or service recommendations.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
16. Usability & Accessibility Factors
✅ Readability Complexity – Is the document easy to understand (Flesch-Kincaid Score)?
✅ Intended Audience Matching – Does the document match the knowledge level of its target readers?
✅ Jargon vs. Layman’s Terms – How much technical or industry-specific language is used?
✅ Translation & Localization Challenges – Phrases or sections that may be difficult to translate.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
17. Influence & Impact Detection
✅ Virality Potential – If this content is likely to be widely shared or quoted.
✅ Market or Industry Disruption – Whether the document suggests major shifts in a field.
✅ Political or Societal Influence – How it may affect policies, activism, or legislation.
✅ Competitive Intelligence – How this document positions against competitors in a market.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B COMPLIANCE ASSESSMENT TOOL
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Regulatory Requirements Extraction
✅ Regulation Name & Jurisdiction – Which law applies (e.g., GDPR, SEC rules, ISO 27001)?
✅ Key Compliance Areas – Security, data privacy, financial reporting, HR policies, etc.
✅ Obligations & Standards – Specific mandates companies must follow.
✅ Penalties for Non-Compliance – Fines, legal actions, reputational risks.
✅ Upcoming Changes – Future amendments, regulatory shifts.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Company Policy Analysis
✅ Policy Title & Scope – Which internal policies apply (e.g., Data Protection, HR Conduct)?
✅ Current Compliance Level – Fully aligned, partially compliant, or non-compliant.
✅ Control Mechanisms – What systems, processes, or technologies enforce the policy?
✅ Enforcement & Accountability – Who is responsible? (Legal team, HR, IT security?)
✅ Review & Update History – When was it last assessed?
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Gap & Risk Analysis
✅ Missing Compliance Areas – Where policies fail to meet regulatory requirements.
✅ Ambiguities or Conflicts – Areas where policies contradict regulations.
✅ Operational Risks – Gaps that could lead to security breaches, fines, or lawsuits.
✅ Financial Risks – Cost implications of non-compliance.
✅ Legal & Reputation Risks – Public perception, legal liabilities, shareholder impact.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Recommendations & Future-Proofing
✅ Immediate Fixes – Quick policy updates to meet current regulations.
✅ Long-Term Adjustments – Strategic changes for evolving regulations.
✅ New Policy Creation – Drafting new policies if none exist.
✅ Monitoring Strategy – How to track compliance over time.
✅ Technology & Automation Needs – Potential AI or software solutions for compliance.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



